                <h4>What <br/>is <br/>CBD?</h4>
                <p>Cannabidiol (CBD) is a naturally occurring compound found in the resinous flower of cannabis, a plant with a rich history as a medicine going back thousands of years. <br><br>Today the therapeutic properties of CBD are being tested and confirmed by scientists and doctors around the world. A safe, non-addictive substance, CBD is one of more than a hundred 'phytocannabinoids', which are unique to cannabis and endow the plant with its robust therapeutic profile.</p>
