                        </div>
                        <div class="text">
                            <h5>Side effects from chemotherapy</h5>
                            <div class="desc">
                                <p>Nausea and vomiting were actually some of the first symptoms to be treated with medicinal cannabis in early clinical trials. By 1990, a survey showed that more than 44 percent of the members of the American Society of Clinical Oncology have recommended the use of cannabis to at least one chemotherapy patient. Studies conducted with rats support the idea that CBD can be equally effective in treating these symptoms. </p>
